<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="415" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="22.[128,1333,1596,2576]" pageId="22" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[130,478,2384,2417]" pageId="22" pageNumber="415">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Olympic Shrew has a relatively wide distribution and can be found in disturbed habitats, indicating that it is tolerant of human activity. Very little is known of its ecology.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
